main event: Radar returns with no known or identifiable source have been noted near Andersen AFB, Guam, from October 1962 to June 1966.
interesting points: Radar data indicate solid material targets involved with instances of unidentified returns,Significant aerial intercepts were attempted but no visual contact was made,FAA controllers and military personnel noted unusual activities and radar phenomena during this period,Many radar sightings occurred at night, suggesting advanced flight capabilities beyond normal aircraft performance,The presence of a Soviet trawler nearby was also mentioned but was deemed unrelated to the sightings.
witness description: Wilfrie F. Gerkin, FAA Supervisory Air Traffic Control Specialist
